records.addlTxt: Sentencing after Revocation held 7-26-18

Defendant Daniel R. Darling in court with attorney Cana G Kohn.  Defendant Daniel R. Darling in custody.  Elizabeth R. Gebert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CF45 and 18CF9 @ 2:52 p.m. Sentencing after revocation on 15CF45. Agreement stated - 15CF45 joining recommendation of DOC. No additions or corrections to revocation packet. 18CF9 Def will waive prelim, information filed, Def will plead to ct 1 and 2, ct 3 dri, ct 4 dismiss and consolidate. Ct 1 - 4 1/2 yrs prison, 2 1/2 yrs ic, 2 yrs es, consecutive to 15CF45. Ct 2 Same sentence, 4 1/2 yrs prison, 2 1/2 yrs ic, 2 yrs es, concurrent to ct 1, consecutive to 15CF45.
15CF45 1 yr ic, 1 yr es, consecutive to 18CF9. Also on 18CF9  ct 1 $600 plus costs, 36 mo revocation, ct 2 costs.
Atty Kohn 15CF45 sentence is concurrent to any other currently serving, 18CF9 consecutive to that. Joint recommendation. No corrections or additions to revocation packet. Def understands and agrees. Prelim waiver reviewed w/Def. Court finds waiver freely & voluntarily made, finds probable cause and binds over. Copy of information received, reading waived. Plea quest. reviewed. Plea to 18CF9 ct 1 - guilty plea, ct 2 - guilty plea. Court grants motion dri ct 3 and dismiss and consolidate ct 4. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Kohn satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds Def guilty of 18CF9 cts 1 & 2. Sentencing remarks by the State. Sentencing remarks by Atty Kohn. Statement by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. Will follow agreement. Orders on 15CF45 ct 1 - 2 yrs prison, 1 yr ic, 1 yr es., concurrent to any sentence currently serving or sentenced on prior to today. Credit for 320 days served. Convert financial obligations to civil judgment.
18CF9 ct 1 - 4 1/2 yrs prison, 2 1/2 yrs ic, 2 yrs es, consecutive to any other sentence including 15CF45. $600 plus costs, DNA surcharge, DNA sample if not already done. 36 month revocation, no IID ordered, alcohol assessment and driver safety plan, credit for 3 days served. Ct 2 - 4 1/2 yrs prison, 2 1/2 yrs ic, 2 yrs es, concurrent to ct 1 but consecutive to any other sentences already serving/sentenced on, including 15CF45. costs, DNA surcharge, Def eligible for SAP, not eligible for CIP. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions. Postconviction rights.
Sentencing hearing on revocation on July 26, 2018 at 02:30 pm.
